ustification":"Single local deterministic mapping function; no module handoff, no I/O, no model dependency.","test_description":"Table-driven unit test over all classifier inputs (including unknown/default guards) asserting exact label output.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.05,"System":0,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"`/kaizen-wip` against live repo and PR state distinguishes clean from stale-no-pr in rendered output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires live repo + live PR state; real git/process/network interactions are part of the failure boundary. Mocks could hide API/auth/serialization/timing mismatches in real status rendering path.","test_description":"Execute `/kaizen-wip` end-to-end in a real test repo with real PR state source (or sandbox org) and assert rendered output shows `STALE` only for branch with unPR’d commits and age beyond threshold.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.92,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Branches with open or merged PRs are not flagged as stale-no-PR false positives.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Core risk is incorrect joining of branch->PR lifecycle state (open/merged) with stale predicate. This is cross-module but can be reproduced with deterministic PR-state fixtures; no required real OS/network in behavior text. Rejected System: no explicit live-infra requirement here.","test_description":"Integration test with wired detector + PR state adapter using fixtures for open, merged, closed-unmerged, and no-PR; assert only no-PR candidates can become stale-no-pr.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Staleness detection remains correct across